<media id="fs-id1167742594230" alt="A diagram of molecular analysis. A circular bacterial genome is shown. Primers bind to repetitive sequences found at multiple locations in the genome. These regions are amplified using PCR. Gel electrophoresis is used to identify the size of the amplified regions. Amplified fragment patters can be compared to known samples to identify strains.">
