<caption>Strains of infectious bacteria, such as <emphasis effect="italics">C. difficile,</emphasis> can be identified by molecular analysis. PCR ribotyping is commonly used to identify particular <emphasis effect="italics">C. difficile</emphasis> strains. Rep-PCR is an alternate molecular technique that is also used to identify particular <emphasis effect="italics">C. difficile</emphasis> strains. (credit b: modification of work by American Society for Microbiology)</caption>
